{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VoUxjGUPcZ31n7WpaWVmxT","type":"tool_result","content":"Stack monitoring data is not showing up in the monitoring cluster.\n\nOBSERVED STATE:\n- Elasticsearch is running in the elasticsearch namespace.\n- Monitoring cluster is running in the monitoring namespace.\n\nYOUR TASK:\nRestore monitoring data flow so the monitoring cluster receives Elasticsearch\nmonitoring data. Stack monitoring covers both a metrics path and a logs path,\nso every Elasticsearch pod must run BOTH a Metricbeat (metrics) and a Filebeat\n(logs) monitoring sidecar that ship to the monitoring cluster.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Do not install CRDs or use operators.\n- Keep the Elasticsearch cluster healthy.\n\nGOAL:\n- Monitoring indices appear in the monitoring cluster.\n- Every Elasticsearch pod runs both a metricbeat and a filebeat monitoring sidecar.====\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n9\n\n[precondition:monitoring_env_ready:preconditionUnits[1] 'monitoring_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n monitoring get pods -l app=monitoring-es 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n0\n\n[precondition:monitoring_env_ready:preconditionUnits[1] 'monitoring_env_ready':apply] $ kubectl delete namespace monitoring --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false\n\n[precondition:monitoring_env_ready:preconditionUnits[1] 'monitoring_env_ready':apply] $ kubectl create namespace monitoring\nnamespace/monitoring created\n\n[precondition:monitoring_env_ready:preconditionUnits[1] 'monitoring_env_ready':apply] $ kubectl -n monitoring apply -f cases/elasticsearch/stack-monitoring-sidecars/resource/monitoring-cluster/\npod/monitoring-curl-test created\ndeployment.apps/monitoring-es created\nservice/monitoring-es-http created\n\n[precondition:monitoring_env_ready:preconditionUnits[1] 'monitoring_env_ready':apply] $ kubectl -n monitoring wait --for=condition=ready pod -l a