{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011r9rqjVzY2iwzckX4oshNs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The oracle passes. The task is complete.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Problem:** Elasticsearch stack monitoring data had stopped flowing to the monitoring cluster — the live ES statefulsets (`es-cluster` ×3, `es-data-new` ×2) ran only the bare `elasticsearch` container with no monitoring sidecars, so no data reached the `monitoring` namespace.\n\n**What I did:**\n1. **Investigated the live state** (workflow-inherited, not the case's standalone defaults): ES is `8.11.1` with security + HTTP TLS (certs at `config/certs`, secret `es-http-tls`), the `elastic` password had been rotated to `elasticpass-elastic-password-next`, and the monitoring cluster is Elasticsearch **7.17.9**.\n2. **Created two ConfigMaps** (`metricbeat-config`, `filebeat-config`) in the `elasticsearch` namespace — Metricbeat uses the `elasticsearch` xpack module against `https://localhost:9200` (CA-verified, `elastic` auth); Filebeat tails `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs/*.log`. Both output to `http://monitoring-es-http.monitoring.svc:9200`.\n3. **Used Beats 7.17.9** to match the monitoring cluster's output version (8.x Beats refuse to ship to a 7.x ES).\n4. **Patched both statefulsets** (strategic merge) to add `metricbeat` + `filebeat` sidecars, a shared `es-logs` emptyDir for the logs path, the TLS CA mount, and the password env — then drove the rolling restart to completion, keeping the cluster healthy.\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- All 5 ES pods are `3/3 Running` (elasticsearch + metricbeat + filebeat).\n- Cluster health is **green** (5 nodes).\n- Monitoring cluster now holds `.monitoring-es-7-mb-2026.06.18` with live documents; Filebeat connection is established and shipping.\n- The case oracle reports **`Stack monitoring sidecars verified` (exit 0)**."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cach